        <num>CC 2642</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 15.  ASSIGNMENT OF RIGHTS
Art. 2642.  Assignability of rights
All rights may be assigned, with the exception of those pertaining to obligations that are strictly personal.  The assignee is subrogated to the rights of the assignor against the debtor.</p>
        </content>
